column1: #Summary1=(human1) In this poem, a traveller recounts deliberating which of two roads diverging in a yellow wood to take, finally choosing the one less travelled by, because it was grassy and wanted wear, and predicts one day telling somewhere that this choice had made all the difference.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) The narrator encounters two diverging paths in a yellow wood and, after much contemplation, chooses the less-traveled road, which ultimately proves to be a life-changing decision that they will reflect upon with a sigh many years later.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) This poem reflects on the narrator's choice at a fork in the road in a yellow wood, opting for the path less traveled, which symbolizes a significant life decision that has ultimately made a profound impact on their life, while acknowledging the inevitability of roads leading to new paths, with the realization they may never return to the original crossroads.
#Summary4=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct) The narrator stands at a fork in a yellow wood, choosing to take the less traveled road, which he reflects will make a lasting difference.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct) The poem describes the narrator choosing the less traveled path in a wood, contemplating how this decision has significantly impacted their life long term, even as they wonder if they will return to their original path someday.
#Text=Two roads diverged in a yellow wood , And sorry I could not travel both And be one traveler , long I stood And looked down one as far as I could To where it bent in the undergrowth ;
#Text=Then took the other , as just as fair , And having perhaps the better claim , Because it was grassy and wanted wear ;
#Text=Though as for that the passing there Had worn them really about the same ,
#Text=And both that morning equally lay In leaves no step had trodden black .
#Text=Oh , I kept the first for another day !
#Text=Yet knowing how way leads on to way , I doubted if I should ever come back .
#Text=I shall be telling this with a sigh Somewhere ages and ages hence : Two roads diverged in a wood , and I — I took the one less travelled by , And that has made all the difference .
